  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Firstly may we offer our condolences to you and your family over the sad loss of your beloved Mum, and thank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us.  
There is no way to prepare for the death of a loved one, and it's really reassuring to hear that you all felt so well cared for and comforted by all the teams involved.  
Memories of the care of your loved one in their last days and hours should be as special as possible, and it is true when it is said that little things mean the most.  
It will be a privilege to share your kind words and lovely comments with our teams who cared for you all.  
We undertake the filming of our patient's experiences here at the trust, in order to share our practices across the organisation, and would like to invite you to participate in a film to share your family's experience.If you feel that this is something you or a family member would consider, please do not hesitate to contact me  
Kind regards  
Kathryn Glass  
Quality support/ Patient Experience Practitioner&lt;/CommentText&gt;
